name: Barbara Zdunk
description:
Burned to death, Prussian Poland, 1811

Barbara is considered to have been the last woman executed for witchcraft in Europe. Although the accusations of witchcraft were listed in her case, witchcraft was not a criminal offense in Prussia at the time

One of a series working with AI to give face to women executed as witches; these form part of a broader collection of Horror Portraits at www.horrorportraits.xyz

#WitchingHourOnHEN 

Can be used as #PFP and #wallpaper

PNG 4800 x 4800
